HEADWORD: Ambigenous
<hw>Am*big"e*nous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambo</ets> both + <ets>genus</ets> kind.]</ety> <def>Of two
kinds.</def> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Partaking of two natures, as the
perianth of some endogenous plants, where the outer surface is calycine,
and the inner petaloid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambigu</ent>⟦br⟧
